# EXPLORATION — {{ question }}

> A light **exploration drawer** for the `{{ question }}` exploration.
> This is the SUB-design primitive that `/explore` opens — the
> front-door to `/design-a-cycle`. It is NOT a bead and NOT a design
> cycle: there is no soundness gate. Its whole job is to converge WITH
> the user on a shared understanding by blending four source tiers:
>
> - **Tier 1** — self / current-context reasoning.
> - **Tier 2** — repo + docs dig.
> - **Tier 3** — web common-usage.
> - **Tier 4** — peer-reviewed literature.
>
> The loop is HYBRID: the light tiers (1 + 2) run in-thread; the heavy
> tiers (3 + 4) are dispatched as a `deep-research` round when the
> question warrants it. Reason in prose in the Inquiry log; precipitate
> each settled result into the Findings section with its provenance.
>
> Lives as ONE MemPalace drawer in the `{{ wing }}/decisions` room,
> tagged `exploration` (tag-not-room). Keep it README-sized.

